org.project

Interface TokensStorage

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    TreeStorage

    public interface TokensStorage
    This interface is used to represent a generic storage for Tokens. Its only features are to order tokens based on their frequency and inserting them.

      • getOrderedTokens

        java.util.Set<java.util.Map.Entry<java.lang.Integer,java.util.List<java.lang.String>>> getOrderedTokens(int maxSize)
        Used to return Tokens ordered by their frequency in insertion operations. Also associates how many insertion operations uses a token.
        Parameters:
        maxSize - max dimension of the set of entries to return.
        Returns:
        a set of entries of integers (frequencies) as indexes and String List(tokens with same frequency) as values.
